Strategy Description
NY Opening Manipulation + Liquidity Sweep + Large FVG Retrace Strategy

Overview
This strategy applies Smart Money Concepts (SMC) logic to capture NY open reversals after a liquidity sweep, using only large Fair Value Gaps (FVGs), a required retrace/test, and a confirmation-based entry.

Core Logic
1) Opening Range (OR)
• OR is defined as 09:30–09:35 (New York time).
• OR High and OR Low are recorded.

2) Opening Manipulation / Liquidity Sweep
• Sweep above OR High = buy-side liquidity taken.
• Sweep below OR Low = sell-side liquidity taken.
• Optional: use first sweep direction only (prevents bias flipping).

3) Large FVG Filter
• FVG size must be at least 5 points.
• FVG must form after the sweep.

4) FVG Test Required
• Price must retrace into the FVG zone (test) before any entry is allowed.

5) Invalidation (No Inversion Before Entry)
• Long setup invalid if price closes below the bottom of the FVG before entry.
• Short setup invalid if price closes above the top of the FVG before entry.

6) Entry Trigger (Confirmation)
Entry occurs when a candle closes:
• Above the higher of (previous candle high, FVG maker candle high) for longs, OR
• Below the lower of (previous candle low, FVG maker candle low) for shorts.

Risk Management
• Stop Loss: 50 points from entry
• Take Profit: 100 points from entry
• Breakeven: stop moves to entry price after price reaches +50 points (50% to TP)

Best Use
• MNQ / NQ
• 1-minute timeframe
• NY session volatility
